The paper addresses the task of cross-domain feature disentanglement using deep generative models, which is a topic related to computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The proposed method is based on generative adversarial networks, which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and multimedia (cs.MM) research. Additionally, the paper involves unsupervised domain adaptation, which is a topic related to neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper are cs.CV and cs.LG, followed by cs.AI, cs.MM, and cs.NE.
